author: Muhammad Zulhusni
description:
Google has employed several key staff team members from Windsurf, a startup known for its AI code generation tools. The move follows failed acquisition talks between Windsurf and OpenAI. Under the deal, Google will pay $2.4 billion in licensing fees to use some of Windsurf’s technology. It won’t take equity or a controlling interest but... Read more »

The post Google hires Windsurf team in a bid to boost AI coding projects appeared first on Developer Tech News.
title: Google hires Windsurf team in a bid to boost AI coding projects
